steps.description:
Then remove the corner box wedges. There will be one located in each corner. Grab each one individually and pull them up and out of the box. They might be a little snug and this is normal. With the wedges removed, the body of the box will be loose. Lift the body of the box up and over the grill. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/39/Webo.jpg/459px-Webo.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/39/Webo.jpg/728px-Webo.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Lastly remove the plastic protector off the grill by lifting if off. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Plast.jpg/460px-Plast.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/6d/Plast.jpg/432px-Plast.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":596,"bigWidth":"432","bigHeight":"560","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

With all of the parts and items removed, the grill body will be as light as it can get. Use the razor and cut the front of the base. Cut each side and follow the arrows and dashed lines as a guide for the cutting locations. Next push down on the front flap of the box base. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b8/Flap.jpg/459px-Flap.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b8/Flap.jpg/728px-Flap.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Now pull the body of the grill forwards with little side to side motions until it is free from the base of the box. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/93/Off-base.jpg/459px-Off-base.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/93/Off-base.jpg/728px-Off-base.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

These were removed earlier, where the orientation should have been noted. Install the flame guard making tabs are facing the back of the grill and set it in place so that it sits securely on the tabs. Install the 3 cooking grates starting with the first one in the far left and then install the following two moving to the right. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/08/Cook-Grate.jpg/459px-Cook-Grate.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/08/Cook-Grate.jpg/728px-Cook-Grate.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Install the warming rack so it sits securely onto the tabs and make sure the raised edge is upwards and closest to the back of the grill. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2f/Warm.jpg/459px-Warm.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/2f/Warm.jpg/728px-Warm.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Locate the 4 pre-attached mounting screws. Loosen the top two screws about half way and remove the bottom two. Attach the burner assembly to the left side by aligning the top mounting holes to the loosened screws. Be careful to make sure to insert the side valve assembly from the side of the grill into the side burner assembly during this process. Tighten the top two mounting screws. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6f/Venturi.jpg/459px-Venturi.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/6f/Venturi.jpg/728px-Venturi.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Re-Install the bottom two screws and tighten to secure the side burner assembly into place. Locate the Igniter lead wire that is taped to the left side of the grill and attach the lead wire to the igniter electrode by firmly pushing it into place. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bf/Ignite-cable.jpg/459px-Ignite-cable.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/bf/Ignite-cable.jpg/728px-Ignite-cable.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Open the right-side door and locate the igniter box. It sits just inside the door on the right-hand side near the top of the cabinet. Remove the igniter cap located on the bottom of the igniter box. Install 1 AA battery with the positive side going into the cap and re-install the igniter cap into the assembly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/14/Igbat.jpg/459px-Igbat.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/1/14/Igbat.jpg/728px-Igbat.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Remove the LED light battery box from the igniter box. Install 2 AA batteries as shown and re-install the battery box into the igniter assembly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0a/Iglight.jpg/459px-Iglight.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/0a/Iglight.jpg/728px-Iglight.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Check that the tank valve is closed before starting. Open the right-side door and locate the tank holder. Flip the tank holding latch to the right so the tank holder can slide out. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/62/FlipR.jpg/459px-FlipR.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/62/FlipR.jpg/728px-FlipR.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Loosen the retention screw on the tank holder. Set the tank to the base sits in the open circle of the tank holder. Make sure the tank is oriented so the valve will face the right side of the tank when pushed back. Tighten the retention screw. Push the tank holder back into place and flip the tank holding latch to the left so the tank hold can't move. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cd/SlideBack.jpg/459px-SlideBack.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/cd/SlideBack.jpg/728px-SlideBack.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}
